.TH "drm_mode_plane_set_obj_prop" 9 "drm_mode_plane_set_obj_prop" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_mode_plane_set_obj_prop \- set the value of a property
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_mode_plane_set_obj_prop
.BI "(struct drm_plane *plane "  ","
.BI "struct drm_property *property "  ","
.BI "uint64_t value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "plane" 12
drm plane object to set property value for
.IP "property" 12
property to set
.IP "value" 12
value the property should be set to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This functions sets a given property on a given plane object. This function
calls the driver's ->set_property callback and changes the software state of
the property if the callback succeeds.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, error code on failure.
